        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>JACOB VOORSANGER&#44;<lb/>
                HOUSTON&#44;<lb/>
                TEXAS.<lb/></p>
            <p>June 9. 1880<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                Rev &#38; Dr Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93;&#33;  On the morning of the 31st<lb/> <del>inst</del> last my wife gave birth to a fine&#44; healthy<lb/> boy Last Monday morning at the &#91;Hebrew&#93; I<lb/> gave him the name of &#91;Hebrew&#93; and in<lb/> English Leon Morais Voorsanger.  I gave him<lb/> the double name of the man whom next to my<lb/> parents I most esteem.  Permit me to express<lb/> the hope that with Heaven&#39;s help my boy<lb/> will become as gifted and pure a man as<lb/> his namesake.  I must offer an excuse<lb/> for writing so late.  The day my baby was<lb/> born I took sick&#8212;the sixth time this<lb/> summer.  Malarial fever has taken a terrible<lb/> hold of me and my health this summer<lb/> is none of the best.  I have been confined to<lb/> my bed until the day of the &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; when<lb/> I was allowed to leave my couch for<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the first time.  To&#45;day I am beginning to gain<lb/> some strength.  I am but the shadow of the<lb/> healthy fleshy looking young man you knew<lb/> but my physician promises to restore my &#34;good<lb/> looks&#34; again with the approach of fall.  He<lb/> claims I am passing through the acclimatization<lb/> process.<lb/></p>
            <p>I must close&#44; having exerted all my little<lb/> strength.  I know you will &#91;&#63;&#93; me in my heart&#39;s<lb/> <sic>prayer&#39;s</sic> for mine &#38; your boy&#39;s welfare.  May God<lb/> Grant he will learn to know you intimately &#38;<lb/> as his father has done profit by your example.<lb/></p>
            <p>Trusting to be honored with a few lines<lb/> in response I remain<lb/></p>
            <p>Sincerely yours<lb/>
                Jacob Voorsanger<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
